urls.description: This work addresses the visibility of feminist demands for justice on Twitter through a selection of 927 tweets generated in Latin American countries, collected and processed using digital techniques. The findings show that of 96 cases, most are unsolved femicides and few achieve high visibility, characterized by immediacy, popularity, and multimedia content. The conclusion is that there are possibilities for positioning the unsatisfied demands for justice but difficulties in gaining visibility, which reduces the strength of the pressure of digital actions on institutions.
